---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About - Paper Lanterns" 
  description="Learn about Paper Lanterns, a curated digital archive preserving historically significant letters and speeches for future generations."
>
  <Navigation />
  
  <main class="about-container">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="about-header">
        <h1 class="about-title">About Paper Lanterns</h1>
        <p class="about-subtitle">
          Preserving the intimate conversations and powerful orations that shaped our world
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="about-content">
        <section class="mission-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">My Vision</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              Before the age of instant communication, every written word carried weight. Letters were deliberate, 
              speeches were crafted with care, and each sentence was chosen with intention. These documents reveal 
              not just historical facts, but the human experiences behind them—the hopes, fears, loves, and dreams 
              of those who came before us.
            </p>
            <p>
              There's something magical about these letters. They are frozen in time yet some continue to travel 
              through time and violently awaken the fullness of human capabilities, while others lie neglected, 
              waiting for someone to rediscover them. Voice from Time is dedicated to preserving and presenting 
              these remarkable documents as they deserve to be seen: as works of art, windows into the soul, 
              and bridges across time.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="team-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Behind the Page</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              Hi, my name is Bhuvan and I'm utterly fascinated by all the treasures available in the public domain. 
              I'm working on a larger project to curate and catalog all the Indian works in the public domain, but 
              I also wanted to collect and publish all the letters in the public domain separately, inspired by the 
              work of Shaun Usher at <a href="https://news.lettersofnote.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Letters of Note</a>.
            </p>
            <p>
              Each letter in this collection has been carefully verified for authenticity and historical accuracy. 
              I believe that these letters and speeches contain timeless wisdom and beauty that should be accessible 
              to everyone, preserved for future generations to discover and rediscover.
            </p>
            <p>
              You can find me on <a href="https://x.com/bebhuvan" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twitter</a> and 
              <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bebhuvan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>. If you know 
              of a remarkable public domain letter that deserves preservation and presentation, or if you have 
              corrections or additional context for existing content, I'd love to hear from you.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="curation-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Curation Philosophy</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              Every letter and speech in our collection has been carefully selected based on five key criteria:
            </p>
            <ul class="criteria-list">
              <li>
                <strong>Historical significance</strong> — Documents that shaped culture, politics, science, or human thought
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Emotional resonance</strong> — Letters that reveal universal human experiences and emotions
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Literary quality</strong> — Beautiful, memorable language that demonstrates the art of expression
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Public domain status</strong> — All content is completely free of copyright restrictions
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Authenticity</strong> — Rigorously verified historical documents with reliable provenance
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="approach-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Our Approach</h2>
          <div class="section-content">
            <p>
              I treat each document as a precious artifact, presenting it with the respect and attention it deserves. 
              My design philosophy emphasizes:
            </p>
            <div class="approach-grid">
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Typography as Art</h3>
                <p>Every letter begins with a beautiful drop cap, and I use premium typography to honor the written word.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Breathing Room</h3>
                <p>Generous whitespace allows readers to focus completely on the text without distraction.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Historical Context</h3>
                <p>I provide just enough background to understand the circumstances without overwhelming the content.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="approach-item">
                <h3>Accessibility</h3>
                <p>Everyone should be able to experience these remarkable documents, regardless of their capabilities.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="collection-stats">
          <h2 class="section-title">What You'll Find</h2>
          <div class="stats-grid">
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">150+</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Historical Documents</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">500+</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Years of History</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">12</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Thematic Collections</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <span class="stat-number">100%</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Public Domain</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>

      <footer class="about-footer">
        <p>All content on Voice from time is in the public domain and freely available to all.</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-container {
    padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .about-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .section-title::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -0.5rem;
    left: 0;
    width: 3rem;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .section-content {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .section-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .criteria-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .criteria-list li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-secondary);
  }

  .criteria-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .criteria-list strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .approach-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .approach-item h3 {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .approach-item p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .collection-stats {
    background: var(--bg-accent);
    padding: 3rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .stat-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .contact-info {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .contact-link {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .contact-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .section-content a {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .section-content a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .about-footer {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-secondary);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-container {
      padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
    }

    .container {
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }

    .about-title {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .about-content {
      gap: 3rem;
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .section-content {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .approach-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .collection-stats {
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .stat-number {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>